00:52:03,540 --> 00:52:06,908
And Bird made his left turn
and went uptown without him.

681
00:52:06,978 --> 00:52:10,779
- Isn't that sick?
- Yeah, very.

682
00:52:10,850 --> 00:52:13,512
- Hey, Bennie, you got a towel for me?
- Yeah.

683
00:52:14,920 --> 00:52:16,650
Thanks.

684
00:52:17,991 --> 00:52:20,756
Maybe I'll just join
a small group in Vegas.

685
00:52:21,762 --> 00:52:24,664
Bennie, what's this I hear
about you getting a job?

686
00:52:24,733 --> 00:52:27,201
I mean, that really upsets me.

687
00:52:27,269 --> 00:52:31,434
- You're kidding, aren't you?
- Very funny, very funny.

688
00:52:32,942 --> 00:52:35,036
Lelia, can I get you
a cup of coffee or something?

689
00:52:35,112 --> 00:52:37,637
No, Hugh.

690
00:52:37,715 --> 00:52:40,116
What's the matter with you?
Are you sick?

691
00:52:43,121 --> 00:52:46,285
You look awful. You ought
to get some rest at night.

692
00:52:46,359 --> 00:52:48,294
Will you shut up!

693
00:52:53,034 --> 00:52:54,968
What did I say?

694
00:52:55,970 --> 00:52:58,030
Just forget it.

695
00:52:58,107 --> 00:53:00,041
I won't forget it. What did I say?

696
00:53:00,109 --> 00:53:03,079
- What's the matter with her?
- Nothing you'd be interested in.

697
00:53:03,146 --> 00:53:06,547
Look, she's my sister too. I wanna know
what's the matter with her.

698
00:53:06,616 --> 00:53:09,814
Nothing, baby. Just a little problem
that came up last night.

699
00:53:09,887 --> 00:53:12,254
A little problem?
What is the little problem?

700
00:53:14,059 --> 00:53:19,054
Look, Bennie. It's just a problem
with the races, that's all.

701
00:53:22,236 --> 00:53:26,503
Like I said, Bennie,
nothing you'd be interested in.

702
00:53:28,543 --> 00:53:30,535
Who all is coming
to this party tonight?

703
00:53:30,613 --> 00:53:32,911
Oh, just some people.

704
00:53:51,004 --> 00:53:52,938
You know what you need?

705
00:53:53,006 --> 00:53:56,272
You need a guy to take care of you
and protect your values.

706
00:53:56,344 --> 00:53:59,212
You need a home and security
and babies, honey.

707
00:53:59,281 --> 00:54:01,215
That's what you need.

708
00:54:02,317 --> 00:54:05,583
<i>- Oh, look. There's Davey Jones. Davey!</i>
- No, Vickie.

709
00:54:05,655 --> 00:54:07,589
Meet Davey. He's wonderful.
You'll love him.

710
00:54:07,657 --> 00:54:10,491
- Vickie, no.
- Davey! Davey Jones. Davey!

711
00:54:10,561 --> 00:54:14,123
Davey, I want you to meet Lelia.
Lelia, this is Davey.

712
00:54:14,199 --> 00:54:16,895
- Hello there.
- Hello.

713
00:54:16,968 --> 00:54:19,767
Sit down for a second, Davey.

714
00:54:21,707 --> 00:54:25,769
Davey went to the same school -
Your brother's school, Stuyvesant.

715
00:54:27,949 --> 00:54:31,909
<i>Vickie-</i>-
<i>How long have you known Vickie?</i>

716
00:54:33,355 --> 00:54:35,653
What do you do all day?

717
00:54:35,724 --> 00:54:39,252
- I paint.
- You're an artist.

718
00:54:40,163 --> 00:54:43,099
Maybe I can drop by one afternoon.
Take in a movie or something.

719
00:54:43,167 --> 00:54:45,568
I don't like the movies.

720
00:54:45,637 --> 00:54:49,437
Well, there are other places to go.
Take you to a club then. How about that?

721
00:54:50,443 --> 00:54:53,310
Or we'll go to an opera.

722
00:54:53,379 --> 00:54:55,314
I might drop up one afternoon.

723
00:54:55,382 --> 00:54:57,373
Maybe we can go for a walk
through the park or-

724
00:54:57,451 --> 00:54:59,386
I don't like the park either.

725
00:54:59,454 --> 00:55:02,014
Oh, give me a break.

726
00:55:09,066 --> 00:55:12,502
- Hi, Dave, daddy.
- Hello, Rupert. How are you?
I'm not interrupting, am I?

727
00:55:12,569 --> 00:55:15,539
Vickie, will you help me out, put in
a good word here or there somewhere?

728
00:55:20,446 --> 00:55:22,573
Well.

729
00:55:22,649 --> 00:55:25,641
- To talk to Lelia.
- Hi, baby. How are you doing?

730
00:55:25,719 --> 00:55:28,587
Why don't you take her
to that wonderful painters' -

731
00:55:28,656 --> 00:55:31,750
They're having some kind of thing
over at Cooper Union.

732
00:55:31,826 --> 00:55:35,456
- She'd love that.
- I wouldn't dig that at all.

733
00:55:35,530 --> 00:55:37,999
Well, that's the kind of thing
I enjoy, you see?

734
00:55:39,335 --> 00:55:42,897
Well, we'll go then.

735
00:55:48,780 --> 00:55:50,714
Lelia. Hello.

736
00:55:50,783 --> 00:55:53,081
I'd like to see you
for a second, can I?

737
00:55:53,152 --> 00:55:55,451
<i>- Yeah, what?</i>
- It's about Tony.

738
00:56:01,996 --> 00:56:06,593
Say, uh, excuse me. Can I talk to Lelia for
just a second? It's something important.

739
00:56:06,668 --> 00:56:09,159
- No, David. I'd rather not.
<i>- Honey. It's okay.</i>

740
00:56:09,238 --> 00:56:12,470
No, please. David,
I don't want to discuss any of this.

741
00:56:12,542 --> 00:56:15,569
- Please. Just come with me for a second.
- No, David, please!

742
00:56:15,646 --> 00:56:19,481
He called me. He was very
upset about something that
happened here the other day.

743
00:56:19,551 --> 00:56:22,884
- And he got me upset about it.
- I know, David.

744
00:56:22,954 --> 00:56:25,856
Yeah, but I feel I'm involved in it.
And I just want to tell you...

745
00:56:25,925 --> 00:56:28,258
that I didn't know at all
what he was like, when, you know -

746
00:56:28,328 --> 00:56:31,320
Hey, hey, Dave, Dave.

747
00:56:31,398 --> 00:56:33,663
Come on, Dave.
Leave my sister alone.

748
00:56:33,735 --> 00:56:36,295
Come on, man.
Come on and join the party.

749
00:56:41,377 --> 00:56:43,312
Look, I have to go.

750
00:56:43,380 --> 00:56:45,314
I'll see you later, all right?

751
00:56:45,382 --> 00:56:48,580
- You're a very good dancer.
- I'm not such a good dancer.

752
00:56:48,653 --> 00:56:50,985
Lelia, come on over here.
Come on over here.

753
00:56:51,055 --> 00:56:53,047
Looks like you and her
are getting along real fine.

754
00:56:53,125 --> 00:56:55,355
Well.

755
00:57:24,597 --> 00:57:27,293
Look, why don't you just
come on and have a drink with us...

756
00:57:27,366 --> 00:57:31,531
and join in the party
and forget about your mood for a while?

757
00:57:31,605 --> 00:57:33,539
You know, I just don't understand.

758
00:57:33,607 --> 00:57:36,441
I think you really
want to join in the party...

759
00:57:36,510 --> 00:57:38,638
but maybe you don't know how.

760
00:57:38,714 --> 00:57:41,182
You want to be coaxed a little bit.

761
00:57:41,250 --> 00:57:43,185
You really feel that way?

762
00:57:44,988 --> 00:57:48,015
I prefer to be coaxed.
But don't you coax me, okay?

763
00:57:48,092 --> 00:57:49,923
There are other ways.

764
00:57:52,731 --> 00:57:55,029
You want a drink?
Want me to get you a drink?

765
00:57:55,100 --> 00:57:58,935
- No, thanks. I don't drink.
<i>- You'll find it's good for what ails you.</i>

766
00:57:59,005 --> 00:58:04,774
<i>Just pull yourself together, because</i>
<i>you're not kidding anybody but yourself.</i>

767
00:58:04,845 --> 00:58:09,783
You know, you have
your sense of values all mixed up.

768
00:58:09,851 --> 00:58:11,786
So I can just -

769
00:58:11,854 --> 00:58:14,288
No, don't touch me.

770
00:58:14,356 --> 00:58:16,587
Come on, just a little taste.

771
00:58:27,439 --> 00:58:30,034
- Let him go, let him go.
- You're crazy, baby.

772
00:58:30,109 --> 00:58:32,976
<i>- Let me go. Let me go.</i>
- Hugh, come on.

773
00:58:33,046 --> 00:58:35,038
Let me go!

774
00:58:38,886 --> 00:58:41,447
<i>What the hell is wrong with that guy?</i>

775
00:58:41,523 --> 00:58:43,514
What's wrong with you?
You don't have to get carried away.

776
00:58:43,591 --> 00:58:45,753
He's always messing up the damn thing!
What's wrong with him?

777
00:58:45,828 --> 00:58:47,989
This is a party! Stop it!

778
00:59:03,984 --> 00:59:07,580
Mary had a little lamb,
its fleece was white as snow.

779
00:59:08,789 --> 00:59:11,280
Everywhere that Mary went,
the lamb was sure to go.

780
00:59:23,574 --> 00:59:26,373
- Gee, he's your brother, and I -
- I know.

781
00:59:26,444 --> 00:59:28,969
I find it hard to believe
you can't talk to him.

782
00:59:29,047 --> 00:59:34,076
I don't know, right now I'd just be satisfied
with a home and a few kids, you know.

783
00:59:34,153 --> 00:59:37,646
- Simple things.
- I envy you.

784
00:59:37,724 --> 00:59:41,183
He's a pretty unhappy kid, you know.
It's too bad you can't -

785
00:59:41,262 --> 00:59:44,026
He's mixed up and for some reason,
I don't know...

786
00:59:44,098 --> 00:59:46,397
he doesn't,
either doesn't want to, is afraid to -

787
00:59:46,468 --> 00:59:48,902
Okay, Hugh.
Let her off the hook, will you?

788
00:59:50,040 --> 00:59:51,405
<i>The night's almost over.</i>

789
00:59:53,376 --> 00:59:55,902
Let's end it off with a little smile
rather than all this.

790
00:59:55,980 --> 01:00:00,384
What's with this "Leave the girl alone"?
Why don't you leave me alone?

791
01:00:00,452 --> 01:00:03,512
I was only attempting to remind you
that we invited her here...

792
01:00:03,588 --> 01:00:05,318
<i>to have a good time, that's all.</i>

793
01:00:05,391 --> 01:00:07,882
She obviously wants to hear
what I have to say.

794
01:00:07,960 --> 01:00:10,691
- Maybe he doesn't wanna talk about it.
<i>- She's not complaining.</i>

795
01:00:10,764 --> 01:00:13,325
Why don't you butt out,
mind your own business?

796
01:00:13,401 --> 01:00:15,995
<i>We want to kill each other,</i>
<i>that's my business.</i>

797
01:00:16,071 --> 01:00:19,371
Every time I turn around, it's you behind
me pushing me, interfering with me.

798
01:00:19,442 --> 01:00:21,535
<i>- You could be replaced.</i>
- You sound pretty mad about it.

799
01:00:21,610 --> 01:00:25,945
Okay, Hugh.
Let's knock it off, huh?

800
01:00:27,952 --> 01:00:29,510
Hey, look.
I'm picking up your phrases.

801
01:00:29,587 --> 01:00:31,920
The other day in Philadelphia
when I was singing...

802
01:00:31,990 --> 01:00:34,015
you know,
I don't appreciate that at all.

803
01:00:34,093 --> 01:00:36,756
<i>- Oh, yeah.</i>
- I'm getting ready to sing the song.

804
01:00:36,830 --> 01:00:38,764
In the middle of the song...

805
01:00:38,832 --> 01:00:42,394
for what reason I don't know
why you did it, you decided to change it.

806
01:00:42,470 --> 01:00:44,438
This don't make sense.
Does that make any kind of sense?

807
01:00:44,505 --> 01:00:48,374
No, I don't think it's fair to...

808
01:00:48,443 --> 01:00:52,540
- sort of as a last minute sort of thing.
- Another little bright idea of his.

809
01:00:52,615 --> 01:00:54,879
Without interfering with you...

810
01:00:54,951 --> 01:00:57,580
I think what you feel more
is my attitude towards life.

811
01:00:57,654 --> 01:01:01,091
<i>Maybe that bugs you, but don't hold it</i>
<i>against me. That's the way I am, see.</i>

812
01:01:01,159 --> 01:01:04,094
How much longer you
planning on us staying here?

813
01:01:04,162 --> 01:01:07,826
- I don't know. What time is it now?
<i>- Five after 5:00.</i>

814
01:01:10,437 --> 01:01:12,405
- Here are your keys.
- Where the hell have you been?

815
01:01:12,472 --> 01:01:14,964
- What the hell do you care?
- What do you mean, "What do I care"?

816
01:01:15,042 --> 01:01:16,976
- There are your keys. Where's Lelia?
- She's out.

817
01:01:17,044 --> 01:01:19,240
Don't mess with me.
I'm splitting. There are your keys.

818
01:01:19,314 --> 01:01:22,147
- I want to talk to you.
- No. Get out of my way.

819
01:01:22,217 --> 01:01:24,686
- I want to talk to you!
- Are you gonna stop it?

820
01:01:24,754 --> 01:01:27,552
Take your hands off!

821
01:01:27,624 --> 01:01:29,286
Look, Bennie, you're my brother.

822
01:01:29,360 --> 01:01:31,760
What do you want me to do,
start the whole thing all over again?

823
01:01:31,829 --> 01:01:34,355
Goddamn it, if I have to whip you,
I'm gonna tell you something!

824
01:01:34,432 --> 01:01:37,402
- Look, wait a minute, will you?
- I'm going.

825
01:01:37,470 --> 01:01:40,098
Bennie, will you listen? I love you.
What the hell am I supposed to say?

826
01:01:41,574 --> 01:01:47,276
<i>Bennie. Bennie, for God's-</i>-
<i>Take the keys, please.</i>

827
01:01:48,349 --> 01:01:50,374
- Bennie.
- All right.

828
01:01:50,451 --> 01:01:54,786
Are we friends?
Buddies? Brothers?

829
01:01:55,958 --> 01:01:57,893
Huh?

830
01:02:06,071 --> 01:02:08,972
- Hi. All ready?
- Well, hello.

831
01:02:09,975 --> 01:02:12,410
No. Where's my flowers?

832
01:02:13,580 --> 01:02:16,345
I was late, so I didn't have
a chance to - I just ran right over.

833
01:02:16,417 --> 01:02:19,147
Well, I just don't think
that's very nice of you at all.

834
01:02:19,220 --> 01:02:23,021
Don't you think you should bring a lady
something when you beg to take her out?

835
01:02:23,091 --> 01:02:25,424
I can go back and get them
if you want me to.

836
01:02:25,494 --> 01:02:27,985
No, just go make yourself comfortable.
There's drinks in there.

837
01:02:28,064 --> 01:02:30,590
- Go, go.
- Will you be long?

838
01:02:30,667 --> 01:02:32,658
I'll be as long as I am.

839
01:02:37,242 --> 01:02:39,302
- Hi, there.
- Oh, hi.

840
01:02:39,378 --> 01:02:41,539
I'm Davey. I'm taking Lelia
to the dance tonight.

841
01:02:41,614 --> 01:02:45,483
Oh, good. Pleased to meet you.

842
01:02:45,552 --> 01:02:50,081
Uh, why don't you go and have a drink
with my brother and Rupe?

843
01:02:50,157 --> 01:02:53,389
- Thanks.
- Introduce yourself, why don't you?

844
01:02:54,930 --> 01:02:57,195
Hi, fellas.

845
01:02:57,267 --> 01:02:59,201
- Hi.
- Hi.

846
01:02:59,269 --> 01:03:02,068
- It doesn't even make sense to be singing.
- I don't want to talk about -

847
01:03:02,139 --> 01:03:03,800
- What?
- What's up?

848
01:03:03,874 --> 01:03:05,808
What's up?
What do you mean, "What's up"?

849
01:03:05,876 --> 01:03:08,107
- You want a drink?
- I'd love one.

850
01:03:08,179 --> 01:03:10,841
- Good, get one over there.
- Yeah, drinks over there.

851
01:03:10,915 --> 01:03:13,248
Over there, man. Drinks over there.
The whole song -

852
01:03:13,319 --> 01:03:16,016
It would sound ridiculous
the other way, you know?

853
01:03:16,089 --> 01:03:18,080
- I'd want to do it, you know -
- Lelia, let's -

854
01:03:18,158 --> 01:03:20,092
I'm not ready, David.
David, I'm -

855
01:03:20,160 --> 01:03:22,095
Do I look ready? No.

856
01:03:22,163 --> 01:03:24,290
Therefore, wait.
Be comfortable and wait.

857
01:03:24,365 --> 01:03:26,300
- Lelia, it's getting late.
- Well, wait.

858
01:03:32,542 --> 01:03:35,034
I'm not gonna say I'm gonna sing
all the things like that.

859
01:03:35,112 --> 01:03:37,842
- Were you just doing "Lucky Day"?
- Yeah.

860
01:03:37,915 --> 01:03:40,146
I know that song.
I'm doing it in my nightclub act.

861
01:03:40,218 --> 01:03:42,152
- Great, man. Great.
- Oh, boy. That's terrific.

862
01:03:42,220 --> 01:03:44,553
No, but really.
I know it, and he's doing it wrong.

863
01:03:44,624 --> 01:03:46,615
Oh, really?
You want to show him how to do it?

864
01:03:46,693 --> 01:03:49,686
That's wrong, man. You're dragging it
through the middle. It's a up tune, man.

865
01:03:49,763 --> 01:03:51,958
- It has to go and swing.
- You tell him, now.

866
01:03:52,032 --> 01:03:55,525
- You know, you know.
- See? Now, that's the right idea.

867
01:03:55,603 --> 01:03:59,768
Oh, wow. Isn't this -

868
01:03:59,842 --> 01:04:03,176
Hey, Bennie. Isn't this great?

869
01:04:05,716 --> 01:04:10,654
Hey, Bennie. Isn't he a smash?

870
01:04:10,722 --> 01:04:13,419
What do you think you're doing?
What do you think you're doing here?

871
01:04:13,492 --> 01:04:16,656
- I was explaining that song.
- I didn't ask you to interrupt
my brother's business.

872
01:04:16,730 --> 01:04:19,062
- He was singing it wrong.
- He makes the money, not you.

873
01:04:19,132 --> 01:04:21,191
<i>- You don't understand.</i>
<i>- What do you mean?</i>

874
01:04:21,268 --> 01:04:24,032
I didn't ask you to come in here
and disturb my relatives.

875
01:04:24,105 --> 01:04:27,007
<i>So please sit down and be quiet.</i>

876
01:04:29,211 --> 01:04:31,874
Did you hear that?
Wasn't it great?

877
01:04:31,948 --> 01:04:34,416
Marvelous.

878
01:04:34,484 --> 01:04:37,079
- Where is he?
- Are you kidding with this guy?

879
01:04:38,889 --> 01:04:40,824
Rupe, I feel -

880
01:04:47,566 --> 01:04:49,626
I'm a strange one.

881
01:05:04,487 --> 01:05:06,421
Would you mind shaking it up, Lelia?

882
01:05:07,424 --> 01:05:09,859
I've been waiting for exactly
two and a half hours.

883
01:05:09,927 --> 01:05:14,456
Do you want to go out with a wreck,
or would you like me to look nice?

884
01:05:15,467 --> 01:05:18,266
I want you to look good, but I want you
to shake it up. Do you mind?

885
01:05:18,337 --> 01:05:20,601
You want to go to the dance with me?

886
01:05:20,673 --> 01:05:24,610
<i>- I wouldn't be here if I didn't want to.</i>
- Then you'll wait. I'm not finished yet.

887
01:05:24,678 --> 01:05:26,612
Hey, hey, what's with you two?

888
01:05:26,680 --> 01:05:29,548
Lelia, do you have to
talk to him like that?

889
01:05:29,617 --> 01:05:32,553
I'll talk-What do you mean,
"Do I have to talk to him that way"?

890
01:05:32,621 --> 01:05:34,714
I wouldn't blame the fella
if he got up and left.

891
01:05:38,795 --> 01:05:41,264
I don't know.

892
01:05:41,332 --> 01:05:43,323
Sure wouldn't let anybody
talk to me like that.

893
01:05:43,401 --> 01:05:46,030
You didn't tell me you had
such a tough sister, man.

894
01:05:46,104 --> 01:05:49,596
- Does she carry on like that
all the time? - Look, I'm just
happy to see her going out.

895
01:05:50,777 --> 01:05:53,302
I'm done.

896
01:05:53,379 --> 01:05:55,905
- How do I look?
- You look nice.

897
01:05:55,983 --> 01:05:58,713
- You be a good boy. Be a good boy.
- Yeah, thank you.

898
01:05:58,786 --> 01:06:02,120
- I'll see you. Write to me.
